name: Vishnu & Garuda
description:
Vishnu is known as "The Preserver" within the Trimurti, the triple deity of supreme divinity that includes Brahma and Shiva. In Vaishnavism tradition, Vishnu is the supreme being who creates, protects and transforms the universe. And He have a Mount, called Garuda.

Garuda is a legendary bird or bird-like creature or God of Bird in Hindu. He is variously the vehicle mount (vahana) of the Hindu god Vishnu. He is younger brother of Aruna, the charioteer of Sun.
